### Typography

#### Families

| Token | Role |
|---|---|
| `--type-family-display` | Headings and display sizes |
| `--type-family-body` | Body text, UI labels, buttons |
<!-- OPTIONAL: has_mono_font -->
| `--type-family-mono` | Code blocks, timestamps, numeric data |

#### Type scale

<!-- PARAMETERIZE: type_scale_table -->

Rules:
- Use `--type-size-sm` for most UI (buttons, labels, form fields, body).
- Use `--type-size-xs` or `--type-size-2xs` for metadata, timestamps, helper text.
- Use `--type-size-lg` and above for headings. Use `--type-size-xl` and above sparingly.
- Never set `font-size` in px. Use only tokens from this scale.

#### Weights

`--type-weight-normal` (400), `--type-weight-medium` (500), `--type-weight-semibold` (600), `--type-weight-bold` (700). Use medium or semibold for emphasis. Reserve bold for display text only.

