### Spacing

Base unit: <!-- PARAMETERIZE: spacing_base_unit -->px. Every spacing token is a multiple of the base unit.

| Token | Value | Common uses |
|---|---|---|
| `--space-1` | <!-- PARAMETERIZE: space_1 --> | Gap between icon and label, input padding (inline) |
| `--space-2` | <!-- PARAMETERIZE: space_2 --> | Tight component padding |
| `--space-3` | <!-- PARAMETERIZE: space_3 --> | Chip padding, compact list items |
| `--space-4` | <!-- PARAMETERIZE: space_4 --> | Standard padding (buttons, inputs, cards) |
| `--space-5` | <!-- PARAMETERIZE: space_5 --> | Section padding |
| `--space-6` | <!-- PARAMETERIZE: space_6 --> | Component gaps |
| `--space-7` | <!-- PARAMETERIZE: space_7 --> | Section gaps |
| `--space-8` | <!-- PARAMETERIZE: space_8 --> | Large layout spacing |
| `--space-10` | <!-- PARAMETERIZE: space_10 --> | Page-level margins |

