### A note on the Tailwind path

This project uses Tailwind. Two consequences for the token system.

**Color and border tokens are wired through `tailwind.config.ts`.** The semantic aliases in `tokens.css` (`--color-brand-primary`, `--color-text-primary`, etc.) map to Tailwind utility names (`bg-brand-primary`, `text-text-primary`) via the `extend.colors` block. Components reference the utilities; the utilities resolve to the tokens. Edit either layer to change a value — they read the same source.

**Spacing and radius use Tailwind's default scale.** `p-4`, `rounded-md`, and `gap-2` resolve through Tailwind, not through `--space-*` and `--radius-*`. The token file still defines these values so they're available in raw CSS contexts (inline styles, non-component CSS), but Tailwind components do not reference them.

If you need to change a spacing or radius value on the Tailwind path, edit `tailwind.config.ts`, not `tokens.css`. Editing only `tokens.css` will leave Tailwind components on the old value and create a silent split. The two scales must agree on the base unit (4px by default).

