## Seed components

### Button

**File:** `app/components/ui/Button.tsx`

**Props:**

| Prop | Type | Default | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `variant` | `"primary" \| "secondary" \| "ghost" \| "destructive"` | `"primary"` | Visual style |
| `size` | `"sm" \| "md" \| "lg"` | `"md"` | Height and padding |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | `false` | Applies `aria-disabled` and visual dimming |
| `children` | `ReactNode` | required | Button label |
| `...rest` | `ButtonHTMLAttributes` | — | Passes through to `<button>` |

**Variants:**
- `primary` — brand-colored background. Use for the primary action on a view.
- `secondary` — outlined. Use for secondary actions alongside a primary.
- `ghost` — no background, no border. Use for low-emphasis actions (close, cancel).
- `destructive` — error-colored background. Use for delete and irreversible actions only.

**Accessibility:** uses `<button>` element; `aria-disabled` on disabled; focus ring via `:focus-visible` using `--color-focus-ring`.

---

### Card

**File:** `app/components/ui/Card.tsx`

**Props:**

| Prop | Type | Default | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `variant` | `"default" \| "elevated" \| "outlined" \| "ghost"` | `"default"` | Shadow and border style |
| `as` | `"div" \| "article" \| "section" \| "li"` | `"div"` | Semantic HTML element |
| `onClick` | `() => void` | — | Makes the card a clickable surface. Adds `role="button"` and keyboard support. |

**Sub-components:** `Card.Header`, `Card.Body`, `Card.Footer` — optional layout slots.

**Accessibility:** when `onClick` is present, adds `role="button"`, `tabIndex={0}`, and `onKeyDown` handler for Enter and Space.

---

### Input

**File:** `app/components/ui/Input.tsx`

**Props:**

| Prop | Type | Default | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `label` | `string` | required | Visible label text. Always required — do not omit for accessibility. |
| `hideLabel` | `boolean` | `false` | Hides label visually; keeps it in the accessibility tree. |
| `error` | `string` | — | Error message. Triggers error state on the input. |
| `hint` | `string` | — | Helper text. Shown when no error is present. |
| `...rest` | `InputHTMLAttributes` | — | Passes through to `<input>` |

**States:** rest, hover, focus, error, disabled.

**Accessibility:** `aria-invalid` when error is present; `aria-describedby` wired to error or hint element; uses `forwardRef` for form library compatibility (React Hook Form, Formik).

